.TH APT-BLITZ 1 "2026-07-04" "0.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
apt-blitz \- multithreaded proxy for APT-like package managers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B apt-blitz
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBapt-blitz\fR is an HTTP forward proxy designed for APT-based Linux
distributions.  It speeds up package downloads by splitting files into
segments and fetching them concurrently, caching results in SQLite-backed
storage with LRU eviction.
.P
Key features:
.IP \(bu 3
Multithreaded download with adaptive segment sizing
.IP \(bu 3
Transparent caching via SQLite with WAL mode
.IP \(bu 3
FTP and FTPS protocol support
.IP \(bu 3
In-flight request coalescing (deduplication)
.IP \(bu 3
YAML configuration file support
.IP \(bu 3
Upstream proxy chaining (HTTP, HTTPS, SOCKS5)
.IP \(bu 3
URL mapping (fake host to real base URL)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-port \fI\,PORT\/\fR
TCP port to listen on.
.br
Default: \fB8080\fR
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_PORT\fR
.TP
.B \-\-bind \fI\,ADDRESS\/\fR
IP address to bind to.
.br
Default: \fB127.0.0.1\fR
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_BIND\fR
.TP
.B \-\-connections \fI\,COUNT\/\fR
Maximum concurrent connections (used by the multithreaded downloader).
.br
Default: \fB4\fR
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_CONNECTIONS\fR
.TP
.B \-\-cache\-dir \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Directory for the SQLite cache database and temporary files.
.br
Default: \fB/var/cache/apt-blitz\fR
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_CACHE_DIR\fR
.TP
.B \-\-max\-cache\-size \fI\,BYTES\/\fR
Maximum cache size in bytes (LRU eviction).
.br
Default: \fB1073741824\fR (1 GiB)
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_MAX_CACHE_SIZE\fR
.TP
.B \-\-config\-file \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Explicit path to the YAML configuration file.
When unset, auto-discovery is used (see FILES section).
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_CONFIG_FILE\fR
.TP
.B \-\-url\-map \fI\,FAKE=REAL\/\fR
Map a fake host to a real base URL.  Multiple mappings
can be specified by repeating the flag or by separating
with commas in the environment variable.
.br
Supported URL schemes: \fBhttp://\fR, \fBhttps://\fR,
\fBftp://\fR, \fBftps://\fR.
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_URL_MAP\fR
.TP
.B \-\-upstream\-proxy \fI\,URL\/\fR
Route all outgoing requests through an upstream proxy.
.br
Supported schemes: \fBhttp://\fR, \fBhttps://\fR,
\fBsocks5://\fR.
.br
Example: \fBhttp://10.0.0.1:3128\fR
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_UPSTREAM_PROXY\fR
.TP
.B \-\-no\-proxy \fI\,HOSTS\/\fR
Comma-separated list of hosts that bypass the upstream proxy.
Accepts domain suffixes (e.g. \fB.local\fR) and CIDR subnets.
.br
Env: \fBPROXY_NO_PROXY\fR
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables override both the YAML config file
and built-in defaults.  CLI flags take precedence over all.
.TP
.B PROXY_PORT
Equivalent to \fB\-\-port\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_BIND
Equivalent to \fB\-\-bind\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_CONNECTIONS
Equivalent to \fB\-\-connections\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_CACHE_DIR
Equivalent to \fB\-\-cache\-dir\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_MAX_CACHE_SIZE
Equivalent to \fB\-\-max\-cache\-size\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_CONFIG_FILE
Equivalent to \fB\-\-config\-file\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_URL_MAP
Equivalent to \fB\-\-url\-map\fR (comma-separated).
.TP
.B PROXY_UPSTREAM_PROXY
Equivalent to \fB\-\-upstream\-proxy\fR.
.TP
.B PROXY_NO_PROXY
Equivalent to \fB\-\-no\-proxy\fR (comma-separated).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I apt-blitz.yaml, apt-blitz.yml
Configuration file in the current working directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/apt-blitz/config.yaml, ~/.config/apt-blitz/config.yml
Per-user configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/apt-blitz/config.yaml, /etc/apt-blitz/config.yml
System-wide configuration file.
.P
Configuration is loaded from the first file found in the order listed
above, unless \fB\-\-config\-file\fR is explicitly provided.
.SH EXAMPLE CONFIGURATION
.nf
.RS
# apt-blitz.yaml
port: 8080
bind: "127.0.0.1"
connections: 8
cache_dir: "/var/cache/apt-blitz"
max_cache_size: 5368709120
url_map:
  \- fake-debian=https://deb.debian.org
upstream_proxy: "http://10.0.0.1:3128"
no_proxy:
  \- .local
  \- 10.0.0.0/8
.RE
.fi
